<paragraph blockId="15.[151,562,151,177]" box="[151,562,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,562,151,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
2. Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Grant, 1955" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1955" box="[268,562,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cranotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[268,405,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cranotettix</emphasis>
Grant, 1955
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,223,430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This genus was described based only in a unique female specimen sampling in 1937 at 
<collectingCountry box="[1131,1220,223,249]" name="Panama" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Panamá</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[1234,1329,223,249]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
Volcano) (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,259,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 36" captionStartId="45.[151,250,942,966]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,918]" captionTargetId="figure-19@45.[151,1436,181,918]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURE 36. Map of approximated occurrence of the genera Cranotettix Grant, 1955 and Plectronotus Morse, 1900." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614466" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614466/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) and named 
<taxonomicName authority="Grant, 1955" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1955" box="[397,745,259,286]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Cranotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpha">
<emphasis box="[397,599,259,286]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cranotettix alpha</emphasis>
Grant, 1955
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[763,850,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[170,1417,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. Cranotettix alpha Grant, 1955 holotype (A) left lateral view, (B) dorsal view, (C) frontal view and (D) labels. Scale bar = 5 mm. Photo of type: Academy of Natural Sciences of Drexel University, Philadelphia/Daniela Silva and Marcelo Pereira." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4614413" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4614413/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). This species is characterized by pronotum which covering over the head and surpassing the apex of the abdomen, almost reaching the apex of the knee; pronotum tuberculate and very lightly scabrous surface; infrascapular area distinctive; tegmina, tegminal sinus and wings lacking; middle femur apical spine absence; hind femur slender, about three and three-quarter times as long as broad (
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[161,309,403,430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="57 - 74" refId="ref22521" refString="Grant, H. J. (1955 a) Systematics of the Neotropical Batrachideine Genera Plectronotus, Halmatettix and Cranotettix gen. nov. (Orthoptera; Acridoidea; Tetrigidae). Proceedings of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 107, 57 - 74." type="journal article" year="1955">Grant, 1955a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, H. J." box="[321,381,403,430]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref22659" refString="Grant, H. J. (1962) A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). PhD Thesis, University of Colorado Library, University of Colorado, Colorado, 208 pp." type="book" year="1962">1962</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
